To me the hurdle seems to be on-boarding the Indian population onto a web 3 platform which has the volume, bandwidth and functionality to scale applications that can lead to mass adoption, only then can we leapfrog the American incumbents if we had to.

Almost every friend of mine knows of web 3 and NFTs, some believe in the value proposition of decentralisation and yet none have the purchasing ability of NFTs that basically are proponents of Web 3 today.

In a country where the median ‚Äúmiddle-class‚Äù salary is around $7500-$14000, how do you reach mass adoption of Web 3 technologies when most of the volume and activity occurs in Ethereum, which is ranging at $2700 as of this writing? 

Add to that 30% Capital gains tax on crypto
NFTs enable ownership to masses, which unlock shared goals, which leads to pockets of communities forming.

Crypto => Centralised control on exchanges => Regulation => small steps

NFTs => Proof of ownership of art with social utility => Buyer‚Äôs Due Diligence as is with any commodity => big strides

This is how India will, or rather should, pioneer Web 3 imo

If India is to leapfrog American incumbents in Web 3, it must have a way to activate its ~ 900 million internet users.

NFTs embrace and allow control over culture, and in a country where independent artists find it hard to make ends meet, NFTs provide means of earning power

The term web 3 itself has gained mass traction over the past year and that is because of NFTs.

While a lot of big names in the space have made their way here from crypto, the market, as big as is it is today, has mostly come into existence because the laymen understood NFTs

India has a massive internet user base & many great open protocols have come out of the country. There is no dearth of vision & skill to pioneer a movement that is web 3. However, the key catalyst is the use of NFTs.

Great time talking Web 3 in India
@balajis , @arunsdevine @shastry, @ashish343 , @Tushar307 

However, was hoping to hear more on #NFTs.
To me, Web 3 is all about decentralised communities having the autonomy to run social organisations through shared ownership üßµ https://t.co/xS4ZRikI9Z
